  "texts": [
    "[6,8,12,13].",
    "Chat GPT 3.5 even failed to use the word \"odontogenic\", while Chat GPT4 did use this diagnostic term.",
    "Higher disagreement in this domain could also be due to the perceived need for a \"precise\" diagnosis, which led to stronger criticism of vague LLM replies.",
    "Another area of concern was illustrated by the significantly higher TDSs for both LLM versions when evaluating the complicated ODS case (Case 3).",
    "For example, ChatGPT 3.5 failed to understand the potential for ODS to cause extra-sinus orbital, intracranial, or osseous infectious complications, and ChatGPT4 still failed to prioritize emergency interventions adequately when compared to the literature [14]."
